                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;For those who might arrive here more than a decade after the question through a search for something else and are confused: JSON-P is now also the name of a Java API for processing JSON, mainly parsing and writing it. It mirrors the XML StAX and DOM APIs, for streaming input/output and document modeling respectively. It supports JSON Pointer for querying, like XPath for XML. I think it also intends to provide the means to transform JSON through JSON Patch, like XML with XSLT and the Java XML Transformer API, but it&apos;s still a bit less advanced than XSLT. This question is about script injection.&lt;/span&gt;

